A nine-year study by the University of Calgary revealed that grizzly bears near Banff National Park have the lowest birth rate in North America.
The study includes policy recommendations and highlights the need for conservation efforts.
Plans to remove grizzlies from the endangered species list in the Yellowstone region have sparked debate among environmentalists.
While some see it as a success story, others fear for the bears' critical habitat.
Federal officials argue that the grizzly population has rebounded, justifying the delisting proposal.
However, concerns remain about the impact on their habitat and future conservation efforts.
